> another variable is compression ratio!
> i  have 6.9:1 on my rebuild (roughly - it was my first time balancing
> heads), and that sucker can get cranked to 35 degrees or so and NOT
ping...
> even when we put it in third and let in the clutch.
> i usually run 90 pump gas.
> 
> now, i know berg says that ping starts before you hear it, so i don't run
> it at that crazy  setting with a centrifugal dizzy, but i could. idle
> timing was like 20! man, what a smooth idle :)
> 
> 
